This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama, issued on December 3, 2015, in response to the attack in San Bernardino, California, that occurred on December 2, 2015. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels of the Federal Government in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its Territories and possessions until December 7, 2015. The flag will also be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad for the same length of time.